  "section_title": "1905\u201306 Ottoman Census statistics -- 1914 Armenian settlements",
  "section_text": "See also : Armenian education in the Ottoman Empire Armenian settlements , churches and schools in 1914 and 1922 : [ 9 ]",
  "uid": "Ottoman_Armenian_population_2",
  "intro": "This article about the Ottoman Armenian population presents some statistics of the Armenian population within the Ottoman Empire. Population size within the empire between 1914 and 1915 is a controversial topic. Most estimates by Western scholars range from 1.5 to 2.4 million. According to Britannica prior to 1915 and Samuel Cox, American Embassy in Istanbul from 1880-1886, it was 1.75 million and 2.4 million, respectively. Establishing the size of this population is very important in determining an accurate estimation of Armenian losses between 1915 and 1923 during the Armenian Genocide."
